		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Color $1D - Black or dark grey?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I recently got a copy of one of my games, and it has a palette tester as an easter egg.  Anyway, on the screen displaying the "D" colors, $0D and $1D both appeared as black (yeah, I know $0D is a bad color.  It didn't cause any problems while looking at it, though) and $2D and $3D were some different greys.
<br />
<br />I think I've heard that $1D is SUPPOSED to be a dark grey, but seeing it on a TV seems to contradict that.
<br />
<br />Is it TV-dependent or is $1D really black?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


